DEFINITIONS

For the purposes of this License Agreement, the following definitions apply: 

Application Software A compiled End-User application software program developed with the proprietary DataFlex language and/or DataFlex Studio and any of its components, resources or libraries.

Business - A Business is an individual person or a legal entity operating as any form of business, proprietorship, partnership, corporation, organization, school, institution, government agency, non-governmental organization, for-profit or not-for-profit entity of any kind whatsoever.

DataFlex Security, Performance, Load Balancing and Failover (SPLF) Server Proprietary DataFlex server software the purpose of which is to enhance the security and performance of one or more DataFlex WebApp application servers while also providing load balancing and failover benefits. 

DataFlex Web Client a user counted license to use the DataFlex WebApp Server as defined herein.

DataFlex WebApp Server Proprietary DataFlex server software, the presence of which is required for the execution and use of web, mobile or other forms of internet, intranet, web services or other internet-based Application Software. 

DataFlex Windows Client Proprietary user counted DataFlex software, the presence of which is required for the execution and use of Windows Desktop Application Software.
 
DataFlex Windows/Web Combo Client The inseparable combination of a DataFlex Windows Client and a DataFlex Web Client licensed as a single Software Product.
 
End User A person who uses Application Software and its required Software Product(s).

Named End User A specific, individual, named person that uses Application Software and its required Software Product(s). Each Named End User must be included in compliance tests for the Number of Named End Users licensed for a particular Software Product.

Number of End Users / Number of Named End Users The count of the total number of End Users or Named End Users licensed to use a Software Product under the terms and conditions of this EULA. 

Number of Web Applications The number of web, mobile or internet Application Software programs licensed for use on a DataFlex WebApp Server. To determine the Number of Web Applications licensed on a server instance, visit: www.dataaccess.eu/pricing.

Privacy Policy Your privacy is important to us. DAE publishes a Privacy Policy (www.dataaccess.com/privacy) that defines how we collect, use, share and protect information. Features in some Software Products send information to or receive information from us during product activation or use. All such collection, sending and receiving of information is performed according to DAEs published Privacy Policy. 

Private Person - A Private Person is a private, individual person not acting as or on behalf of a public or private business, organization, school, for-profit or not-for-profit entity of any kind whatsoever.

Server Instance A network operating system environment installed a) directly on a physical hardware server or b) on a virtual server, including a cloud server instance, that is configured to share resources among multiple End Users computers or devices that are connected to it. Non-running, stored virtual Server Instances require licenses as defined in the Software Product Price List or Product Information Document. A specific connection technology is not consequential to the definition of a Server Instance; the existence of multiple End User device connections and the sharing of resources are the essence of a Server Instance for the purposes of this EULA. For licensing purposes, every installation of a Software Product on any Server Instance requires an individual, unique, Software Product serial number and registration code even if multiple virtual Server Instances are installed on the same physical hardware server.

