2.2 COMMERCIAL LICENSE FOR DATAFLEX WEB CLIENT: DataFlex Web Clients are required to deploy and execute internet-based Application Software on desktop web browsers and mobile devices. This license entitles a specific Number of Named End Users to access and use web Application Software on a DataFlex WebApp Server. Web Client licenses may not be shared among End Users each Named End User of the web Application Software must have an individually assigned Web Client license. In its sole discretion, DAE may grant licenses for multiple instances of DataFlex WebApp Server to support a large Numbers of Named End Users. Each installed DataFlex WebApp Server used with DataFlex Web Clients must have a unique serial number and registration code provided by DAE. Contact DAE to request additional DataFlex WebApp Server licenses for high-demand Web Client environments.

2.3 COMMERCIAL LICENSE FOR DATAFLEX WINDOWS/WEB COMBO CLIENT: The DataFlex Windows/Web Combo Client license is an entitlement for a defined Number of Named End Users to use both a Windows Client and a Web Client according to their respective license definitions, entitlements and limitations. Windows/Web Combo Clients may not be shared among users each End User must be uniquely named and must have an individually assigned Combo Client license. Windows/Web Combo Client Licenses are inseparable and may not be unbundled to enable the licenses to be used by different End Users.

